Wenda Johnson is a renowned rodeo contestant and barrel racer, known for her exceptional skills and achievements in the sport. She is a four-time Wrangler National Finals Rodeo qualifier and has made significant strides in her career since she started barrel racing professionally in 2018.

Here you can follow Wenda Johnson’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Wenda Johnson

Wenda Johnson was born in 1985 and hails from Pawhuska, Oklahoma. She is the daughter of Victor and Janiece Wilson, both of whom were involved in rodeo when they were younger.

Johnson is married to Tyson J Johnson, the manager of the 70,000-acre cattle ranch named Deseret Ranches in Pawhuska, Oklahoma. Together, they have two daughters, whom they are raising to be strong women.

Early Life

Johnson grew up in Arizona, where horses were a consistent part of her life from the beginning. Her mother, Janiece Wilson, introduced her and her sister to horses while they were living in Cave Creek, Arizona.

Johnson’s mother taught her how to handle horses at any speed, which helped Johnson develop the skills and confidence to compete as one of the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association’s top barrel racers.

Professional Career

Johnson started barrel racing professionally in 2018. In 2020, she made a significant leap in her career, finishing the year ranked 12th with $90,569 in earnings.

In 2021, she won several tournaments, including the Reno Rodeo, San Angelo Stock Show, and Rodeo, and Coleman PRCA Rodeo.

As of 2023, she is a four-time Wrangler National Finals Rodeo qualifier and has earned over $120,506 in the regular season.

Wenda Johnson’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Wenda Johnson’s estimated net worth is $1 million.

She has earned significant income from her rodeo career. In 2023 alone, she earned over $120,506 in the regular season.

Career Earnings

Johnson’s career earnings have seen a steady increase since she started barrel racing professionally. In 2019, she earned $7,893, and by 2020, she had earned $90,569. In 2023, her regular-season earnings were over $120,506.

Personal Details

Husband

Wenda Johnson is married to Tyson J Johnson, the manager of the 70,000-acre cattle ranch named Deseret Ranches in Pawhuska, Oklahoma.

How Old is Wenda Johnson?

As of 2023, Wenda Johnson is 38 years old.

What is her nationality?

She is American.

FAQs About Wenda Johnson 

What is Wenda Johnson’s net worth?

Her estimated net worth is $1 million.

When did she start barrel racing professionally?

Wenda started barrel racing professionally in 2018.

How many times has she qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo?

As of 2023, she has qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo four times.
